## What to add

### 1. New handler function — insert just before line 1634 (before `common_chat_try_specialized_template`)

```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v0.3 - [INST]/[/INST] user turns, system prepended to first user turn, </s> after assistant.
// No tool-call or reasoning tokens; [SYSTEM_PROMPT] is absent (that marker belongs to the Ministral/v7 family).
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &              tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params &     inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    data.prompt            = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format            = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.supports_thinking = false;

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        return p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt) + p.content(p.rest());
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();
    return data;
}
```

- Uses `common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs)` (no messages override) so the Jinja template's own logic handles where the system message is injected.
- Content-only PEG rule — v0.3 has no `[TOOL_CALLS]` or reasoning tags.
- `supports_thinking = false`.

