### 2. Registration — insert just before `return std::nullopt;` at line 1690 of `common_chat_try_specialized_template`

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 - [INST]/[/INST] format, no [SYSTEM_PROMPT].
    // Placed last so all more-specific handlers (Ministral 3, etc.) take priority first.
    // Key distinguisher from Ministral 3: absence of [SYSTEM_PROMPT].
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos && src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: mistral-instruct-v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

**Why no conflicts:** Ministral 3 requires `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` to be *present*; all other handlers check entirely different tokens (`<|channel|>`, `>>>all`, `<|tool_calls_section_begin|>`, etc.). Placing this condition last lets every more-specific handler win first.

